nt for the seriousness of Alarcón's theatre - his challenge to his audience to think hard and clear about his play, particularly over the issue of illusion, deception and dissimulation - Whicker focuses on the moral arguments perceived in Alarcón's theatre, and their reference to serious literary-moral issues current in the Golden Age; he tests the relevance of his argument against contemporary circumstances, the ethics ofprivanza in particular. JULES WHICKER lectures in the department of Hispanic studies, University of Birmingham.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aHispanic Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / Hispanic American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846153624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846153624/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles